---
import img2 from '../../assets/images/maquina2.png';
import img3 from '../../assets/images/AsphaltPlant/bin1.png';
import img4 from '../../assets/images/AsphaltPlant/bin2.png';
import img5 from '../../assets/images/AsphaltPlant/drum3.png';
import LearnBtn from '../unitComponents/LearnBtn.astro';
import Image from 'astro/components/Image.astro';
---
<div class="w-full flex flex-col items-center justify-center font-bold mt-0 md:mt-20">
    <div class="bg-blueMain text-white gap-4 flex flex-col md:flex md:flex-row w-full justify-between items-center px-4 pt-4 md:p-8">
        <h1 class="lg:text-4xl text-2xl text-start w-full">From 10 or 20 tons</h1>
        <Image src={img5} alt="" class="md:w-[50%]">
    </div>
    <div class="justify-end grid grid-cols-12">
        <div class="hidden lg:block col-span-4"></div>
        <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-7 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 bg-blueMain lg:rounded-b-2xl px-4 pb-4 pt-2 md:p-8">
            <div class="col-span-1">
            <h1 class="lg:text-4xl text-xl text-redBg">
            TRIASO®<br> <span class="text-white">BIN UNITS</span>
            </h1>
            </div>
            <div class="col-span-2">
                <p class="lg:text-lg text-base text-grisSubP">High-quality equipment built for durability and efficient material handling.
                With reinforced steel structures and advanced vibration systems, they ensure optimal performance, 
                minimal wear, and reduced maintenance, while delivering consistent, reliable results in demanding
                environments.
            </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1 hidden lg:block"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-8 lg:px-52 lg:text-xl text-base font-normal mt-10">
        <h1 class="text-center text-grisT">Triaso® Bin Units are essential for efficient material handling in various industrial
             applications. Designed for optimal storage and transfer of aggregates,
              they ensure reliable performance in demanding environments. Ideal for asphalt plants,
               aggregate processing, and related applications, these units feature durable construction
                and customizable configurations. They provide smooth material flow, low maintenance, 
                and long-lasting performance, making them perfect for the asphalt industry.
        </h1>
        <h1>AQUI VA EL VIDEO</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col items-start justify-center mt-10 px-8 lg:px-52 text-grisT">
        <h1 class="text-xl lg:text-4xl text-black">Dosing System</h1><br>
        <h2 class="text-base lg:text-xl">The dosing system in these bin units is designed to ensure precision and efficiency 
            in material handling. Here are the key features:
        </h2><br>
        <ol class="pl-8 font-normal list-disc text-base lg:text-xl space-y-4">
            <li>Precise Motor Control: Allows for fine adjustments of up to 1 rpm, ensuring
                 accurate dosing of materials.
            </li>
            <li>Improved Discharge System: Prevents stone accumulation and jams between rollers, 
                maintaining a consistent flow.
            </li>
            <li>Adjustable Discharge Gates: Each bin is equipped with gates that can be adjusted according 
                to material requirements.
            </li>
            <li>
                Automatic Dosing System: Synchronized with the production rate, 
                it ensures consistent material proportions, even with changes in work pace.
            </li>
            <li>24" Collector Belt: Receives material from individual belts of each bin,
                 optimizing dosing and material flow.
            </li>
            <li>Material Flow Control: Sensors automatically activate or deactivate the vibrator based on material flow, 
                preventing issues such as empty runs or uneven distribution.
            </li>
        </ol>
        <h2 class="mt-8 text-base lg:text-xl">This system guarantees precise and efficient dosing, essential for smooth operations and high-quality
             output in bin units.
        </h2>

    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col md:grid md:grid-cols-2 justify-center my-5 md:my-10">
        <div class="flex justify-center items-center w-full">
            <div class="bg-blueMain md:rounded-r-2xl py-10 px-8 md:px-16 min-h-1/2">
                <h1 class="text-white font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl">Seamless Integration with <br>Other Systems</h1>
                <br>
                <p class="text-grisSubP text-sm md:text-lg font-bold">
                    Triaso® asphalt plants are designed to integrate seamlessly with bins, conveyors, asphalt tanks, 
                    etc. 
                    This enables synchronized operations and a consistent flow of hot-mix across your processing
                     system.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full">
                <Image src={img2} alt="" class="object-cover w-full">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center mt-10 px-8 lg:px-52 text-black gap-10">
        <h1 class="lg:text-3xl text-lg">Fully Customizable Bin Units</h1>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-0 md:gap-10 lg:gap-44">
            <ul class="pl-8 list-disc text-sm md:text-lg">
                <li>Grizzlies</li>
                <li>Bin level indicators</li>
                <li>Adjustable depth control gates</li>
                <li>Cable trays</li>
                <li>Bulkheads <span class="hidden md:block">(available in full height)</span></li>
                <li>Self-relieving feeder throats</li>
                <li>Bin dividers</li>
                <li>Walkways</li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="pl-8 list-disc text-sm md:text-lg">
                <li>Bin covers</li>
                <li>Built-in retaining walls</li>
                <li>Air cannons</li>
                <li>Moisture probes</li>
                <li>Wire mesh guarding</li>
                <li>Bin vibrators</li>
                <li>Bin extensions</li>
                <li>Built-in scalping screens</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <LearnBtn />
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 items-center justify-center mt-10 gap-10">
        <div class="flex flex-col text-grisT items-center justify-center">
            <h1 class="lg:text-2xl text-xl mb-4 text-start w-full px-8 lg:pl-52">RAP BINS</h1>
            <p class="lg:text-lg text-base mb-4 text-justify px-8 lg:pl-52">Triaso® RAP Bins are designed to efficiently handle and transport recycled 
                asphalt pavement (RAP) in asphalt plants. Built for durability, they ensure 
                a consistent and reliable flow of material, enabling seamless integration 
                into your plant's production process. With their robust construction, Triaso® 
                RAP Feeders can handle the heavy, abrasive nature of RAP, reducing downtime and 
                ensuring high operational efficiency.</p>
                <Image src={img3} alt="" class="block md:hidden">
            <LearnBtn />
        </div>
        <Image src={img3} alt="" class="hidden md:block px-8 lg:pr-52">
        <Image src={img4} alt="" class="hidden md:block px-8 lg:pl-52">
        <div class="flex flex-col p-4 text-grisT items-center justify-center px-8 lg:pr-52">
            <h1 class="lg:text-2xl text-xl mb-4 text-start w-full">Powder Additives Feeders</h1>
            <p class="lg:text-lg text-base mb-4 text-justify">Triaso® Powder Additives Feeders provide efficient and reliable storage 
                and dispensing of powder-based materials. Designed for easy integration with your existing 
                systems, they ensure consistent flow and precise dosing of additives, 
                improving overall production efficiency with minimal maintenance.</p>
                <Image src={img4} alt="" class="block md:hidden w-full">
            <LearnBtn />
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 items-center jsutify-center mt-10 lg:gap-44">
        <div class="bg-blueMain p-8 lg:rounded-r-2xl">
            <h1 class="text-white lg:text-3xl text-xl">Optimized for Efficiency and Safety</h1><br>
            <p class="text-grisSubP lg:text-lg text-base text-justify">Triaso® Bin Units are engineered not only for efficiency but also for safety. 
                Their design includes features that minimize the risk of material spillage or buildup, 
                contributing to a safer working environment. Easy-to-operate discharge mechanisms and 
                strategically placed access points ensure that maintenance and material loading can be 
                performed safely and efficiently, reducing downtime and enhancing workplace safety standards.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-grisT p-8 lg:rounded-l-2xl">
            <h1 class="text-white lg:text-3xl text-xl">Efficient Bulk Storage</h1><br>
            <p class="text-grisSubP lg:text-lg text-base text-justify">Triaso® Bin Units provide an efficient
                 and organized way to store bulk materials, ensuring quick and easy access for loading and 
                 transfer. With their large capacities, these units are ideal for storing aggregates, 
                 recycled materials, and other bulk substances in a compact and organized manner, 
                 for asphalt plants, they help to streamline material handling, reducing storage space 
                 requirements while maintaining high operational efficiency.
                </p>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>